LAFIA – The Federal Government’s Value Chain Development Programme (VCDP), being implemented in Nasarawa State, in collaboration with the International Fund for Agricultural Development (IFAD) was to provide more funds for the rebuilding of Agricultural processing centres in the state. Hajiya Fatima Buhari, the Head, Market Enterprise Development Unit of VCDP, said this duringa 3 -day assessment visit to Nasarawa State to assess the level of implementation of the programme in the state. Speaking in Doma Local Government Area( LGA) of the state while inspecting market stores, solar-powered borehole and rice processing centre, Hajiya Buhari expressed satisfaction at the level of implementation of the programme. Stop Chasing Shadows, Nnamdi Kanu Is Not Your Problem, Rita… Real Madrid Secure First Refusal ‘Agreement’ For… She maintained that the Federal Government was working out modalities to rebuild some of the Agricultural processing centres in the state, She add that, “We are here to assess the level of implementation of the support mission for our beneficiaries” “The visit is to check on our project work that we have done and how they are being maintained”. “So far, the assessment is very good. The beneficiaries are trying in the maintenance and we might likely come again to help rebuild some of the processing centres”. She said. Also speaking, the State Programme Coordinator, Dr. Eunice Adgidzi said the project was aimed at improving the livelihood of small-scale rice and farmers in the locality and the state at large.